# Sudoku Solver — Image Recognition & Roadmap

Add image-based input to the existing Sudoku solver so a user can provide a cropped Sudoku grid image instead of typing 81 values manually. Also add solve-time measurement and write a comprehensive roadmap document explaining the project evolution.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Tesseract OCR is required.** The image recognition feature depends on `libtesseract` being installed on your Mac. You can install it via Homebrew:
> ```
> brew install tesseract
> ```
> Please confirm you have (or are willing to install) Tesseract before I proceed.

> [!NOTE]
> The approach assumes the input image is a **cleanly cropped photograph or screenshot** of a Sudoku grid. Grid detection uses a simple uniform 9×9 subdivision (no perspective correction or Hough line detection) since you mentioned the images will be "perfectly cropped."

## Proposed Changes

### Solver Core (refactored from Algorithm.c)

#### [MODIFY] [Algorithm.c](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/Algorithm.c)

- **Extract solver functions** ([printMatrix](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/Algorithm.c#9-17), [isValid](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/Algorithm.c#21-54), [findEmptyCell](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/Algorithm.c#58-68), [solveSudoku](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/Algorithm.c#72-100)) into a separate `solver.h` / `solver.c` pair so they can be reused by both input modes.
- **Add timing** — wrap the [solveSudoku()](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/Algorithm.c#72-100) call with `clock()` from `<time.h>` to measure and print elapsed time in milliseconds.
- **Add dual input modes** — accept a CLI flag:
  - `./sudoku` → manual scanf mode (existing behavior)
  - `./sudoku --image <path.png>` → image recognition mode

