### New Files

#### [NEW] [solver.h](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/solver.h)

Header declaring the solver API:
- `void printMatrix(int matrix[9][9])`
- `bool isValid(int matrix[9][9], int row, int col, int num)`
- `bool findEmptyCell(int matrix[9][9], int *row, int *col)`
- `bool solveSudoku(int matrix[9][9])`

#### [NEW] [solver.c](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/solver.c)

Implementation of the solver functions (moved from [Algorithm.c](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/Algorithm.c)).

#### [NEW] [image_reader.h](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/image_reader.h)

Header declaring:
- `int readSudokuFromImage(const char *imagePath, int matrix[9][9])`

#### [NEW] [image_reader.c](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/image_reader.c)

Image processing pipeline:
1. **Load image** using `stb_image.h` (single-header, bundled in project)
2. **Convert to grayscale** if not already
3. **Divide into 9×9 grid** — compute cell width = `image_width / 9`, cell height = `image_height / 9`
4. **For each cell:**
   - Extract cell region as a sub-image
   - Apply binary thresholding (pixel > 128 → white, else black)
   - Check if cell is empty (count dark pixels; if below threshold → cell = 0)
   - If not empty → pass cell image to **Tesseract** via the C API (`TessBaseAPISetImage`, `TessBaseAPIGetUTF8Text`) with whitelist `"123456789"` 
   - Parse recognized character → integer (1–9), or 0 if recognition fails
5. Return the populated 9×9 matrix

#### [NEW] [stb_image.h](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/stb_image.h)

The public-domain [stb_image](https://github.com/nothings/stb) single-header image loader. Downloaded and bundled.

#### [NEW] [stb_image_write.h](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/stb_image_write.h)

Used to write individual cell images to temp files for Tesseract processing.

#### [NEW] [main.c](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/main.c)

Unified entry point:
```c
int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    int matrix[9][9];
    
    if (argc >= 3 && strcmp(argv[1], "--image") == 0) {
        // Image mode
        readSudokuFromImage(argv[2], matrix);
    } else {
        // Manual mode (scanf)
        manualInput(matrix);
    }
    
    printf("Initial Sudoku puzzle:\n");
    printMatrix(matrix);
    
    clock_t start = clock();
    if (solveSudoku(matrix)) {
        clock_t end = clock();
        double elapsed = (double)(end - start) / CLOCKS_PER_SEC * 1000.0;
        printf("\nSolved Sudoku puzzle:\n");
        printMatrix(matrix);
        printf("\nTime to solve: %.3f ms\n", elapsed);
    } else {
        printf("\nNo solution exists!\n");
    }
}
```

#### [NEW] [Makefile](file:///Users/devanshkhosla/Projects/Suduko%20Solver%20C%20with%20Scan%20/Makefile)

Build system using `gcc`:
```makefile
CC = gcc
CFLAGS = -Wall -O2 $(shell pkg-config --cflags tesseract)
LDFLAGS = $(shell pkg-config --libs tesseract) -lm
SRCS = main.c solver.c image_reader.c
TARGET = sudoku

$(TARGET): $(SRCS)
	$(CC) $(CFLAGS) -o $(TARGET) $(SRCS) $(LDFLAGS)

clean:
	rm -f $(TARGET)
```

